Recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed on the following:
The Municipal Treasurer to send written notices to the concerned payees about the existence of a stale check and determine the validity of their claim;
The Municipal Treasurer to issue new checks as a replacement of stale checks if a valid claim exists due to the concerned payee;
The Municipal Accountant to provide adjusting entries to cancel the stale check; and
The Municipal Treasurer to strictly observe the guidelines in the monitoring of outstanding checks.

Recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed of the following:
The Market Supervisor with the supervision of the Municipal Treasurer, demand for the immediate payment of the delinquent accounts including surcharges and interests. Otherwise, cause the immediate cancellation of the lease contracts with the stall owners and apply all other sanctions provided for in the Local Revenue Code and the Memorandum of Agreement/Lease Contract;
The Municipal Treasurer to direct the Market Supervisor of the proper recording and monitoring of the account to provide a more complete and reliable report as also expected from an accountable officer of the municipality;
The Municipal Mayor enforce the strict implementation of the Revenue Code; and
The Municipal Accountant draw the Journal Entry Voucher to record the accrued income from market stall rentals and submit a copy to the Auditor.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Management require:
The Inventory Committee to conduct semestral physical count of inventories and submit the result of the physical count using the Report on the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) to the Office of the Auditor not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively;
The General Services Officer to prepare and maintain the stock cards for each supply/inventory item and periodically reconcile the same with the accounting records and the result of the physical count;
The Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain the Supplies Ledger Cards (SLC) for each supply/inventory item and periodically reconcile the same with the supply records and the result of the physical count, as well as provide the appropriate disclosures in the notes to financial statements pursuant to Paragraph 47 of IPSAS 12 including, but not limited to, the amount of inventory recognized as expenses during the year; and
The Municipal Accountant to prepare necessary journal entries to reflect the correct balance of the inventory accounts and to furnish the Auditor a copy of the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) taking up the adjustments.

Recommendations:
We recommended the following:
Management to direct the department in-charge to give priority to the registration of these 16 parcels of land in the name of the LGU of Sominot under the Torrens Title System;
Municipal Assessor to sort the documents and provide a copy/list of the Deed of Sale of these Lands with the corresponding Purchase Price to the office of the Municipal Accountant and the latter to record the same in the book as addition to the Land Account;
Municipal Accountant to update the SL disclosures with details that can at least aid the departments, especially during the conduct of inventory, in identifying the corresponding titles on each item disclosed; and
The Municipal Mayor to direct the office of the Municipal Assessor to forward the TCT/OCT to the office of the Municipal GSO for safekeeping, as the scope and function of the latter includes the same.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Management require the:
Accountable Officer to restitute the remaining ₱364,007.52 unremitted collections;
Former Municipal Treasurer to produce the amount of ₱317,089.60 representing partial payments directly made to her by the AO;
Liquidating Officer to be more stern in the maintenance of her logbook with regards to the Accountable forms received, issued and consumed as part of the monitoring and control measures, as well as to safeguard the accountable forms against its possible misuse;
Current Municipal Treasurer to account and deposit the unremitted collections, as well as monitor all collectors as to compliance of Section 29, NGAS Manual for LGUs regarding remittance of their collections; and
Municipal Accountant to prepare necessary journal entries to account for the understatement of the income account representing the unaccounted collections of the AO.

